description.narrative: 1. Screening. 2. Emodepside: advance the clinical development of emodepside as an anti-parasitic macrofilaricidal treatment. 3. Develop a macrofilaricide candidate for filarial diseases. 4. TylAMac (ABBV-4083): advance the clinical development of TylAMac as a macrofilaricidal treatment that targets Wolbachia bacteria. 5. Oxfendazole: advance the clinical development of oxfendazole as an anti-parasitic macrofilaricidal treatment.
DNDi aims to deliver a safe effective affordable and field-adapted drug that can kill adult filarial worms (a ‘macrofilaricide’) and be used for prevention or individual treatment.
